name: sfchronicle
text: Habibi, a pop-up in Russian Hill’s Bacchus, is proof that wine bars can make sense under pandemic-era safety precautions. Named for an Arabic term of endearment, the welcoming bar dips a toe into natural wine, writes @Esther_Mobley. https://t.co/Nw2dP8S20y

text:
RT @SFC_Datebook: For months, we’ve been watching movies and TV shows shot before things changed. @Netflix's #SocialDistance lets us know that life and creativity are still going forward even while we’re still dealing with the pandemic.

Read @MickLaSalle's review here: 
https://t.co/yEnLrK0rxL

name: sfchronicle
text:
Mike Yastrzemski, like all rookie phenoms, needed a sophomore season to prove he was no fluke. That he did.

The next question is, how long can the Giants right fielder keep it up, given he is not a young man in the lifespan of a baseball career. https://t.co/SR0Wbfj1bq

name: sfchronicle
text: The California ISO is encouraging residents across the state to conserve electricity from 3 p.m. to 10 p.m. Thursday, due to potential stress on the electricity grid from hot temperatures. https://t.co/lZvZtnkSao

name: sfchronicle
text:
It’s fair to say the #49ers’ rash of injuries are the biggest factor in their 2-3 start. But many of the most impactful injuries have been suffered by injury-prone or rehabbing players they’ve signed or drafted over the past two seasons.

via @Eric_Branch: https://t.co/XwcTs7n86x
